    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1052"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1052">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1834</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to your personal
                    note of October 12, 1915, relative to the alleged shipment by parcels post from
                    New York to Germany and Austria of mineral slag, rubber, and shoes, I beg to
                    advise you that the Department is now in receipt of a letter from the Postmaster
                    General, communicating a report from the postmaster at New York, in which it is
                    stated that no parcels containing printing material compound or rubber stamp
                    material have been shipped through that office to Germany; but that mineral
                    slag, not being included in the contraband list of your Government, parcels said
                    to contain that product have been sent by parcels post to Germany.</p>
                <p>The postmaster stated also, that shoes being on the conditional contraband list
                    have not been considered as prohibited and that parcels containing shoes have
                    been shipped to private parties in Germany and Austria.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
